net.casper.ext.narrow

Class CBuildNarrowedFile

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.casper.ext.narrow.CBuildNarrowedFile
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    net.casper.data.model.CBuilder

    public class CBuildNarrowedFile
extends Object
implements net.casper.data.model.CBuilder
    Convenience builder that loads a file using CBuildFromFile and narrows it at the same time using CBuildNarrowed. Useful for applying to files that have been created from sources that have no data type associated with columns (e.g. CSV files) or loosely specified data types (eg. Excel files) and the data type can't be specified at the time of loading. Missing integer or double values will be treated as Strings, unless setConvertMissing(boolean) is true in which case they will be converted to CellReaders.MISSING_VALUE_INTEGER or CellReaders.MISSING_VALUE_DOUBLE instead.
    Version:
    $Revision: 181 $
    Author:
    Oliver Mannion

      • CBuildNarrowedFile

        public CBuildNarrowedFile(File file,
                  String primaryKeys)
                   throws IOException
        Create narrowed delimited file builder using default delimiter settings. Container name is the file name and will read column header from the file. Missing values are converted during narrowing.
        Parameters:
        file - file
        primaryKeys - null if no primary key otherwise the column names of primary keys, separated by comma, eg: "firstname,lastname" NB: do not include a space after the comma.
        Throws:
        IOException - if IO problem reading file header.

      • CBuildNarrowedFile

        public CBuildNarrowedFile(File file,
                  String containerName,
                  String[] columnNames,
                  String[] primaryKeys)
                   throws IOException
        Construct a narrowed casper delimited file builder.
        Parameters:
        file - file
        containerName - if null will use default (the file name)
        columnNames - the name of the columns in the file. If null, column names will be loaded from the file header. If specified then the file must have a header with the same columns names (case and order insensitive).
        primaryKeys - null if no primary key otherwise an array of primary key names
        Throws:
        IOException - if IO problem reading file header.
